TY  - JOUR
T1  - Management Perspective: Gastro-Economic Cycles
AU  - Goetz, Billy E.
Y1  - 1964/12/01
PY  - 1964
DA  - 1964/12/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/254941
DO  - 10.5465/254941
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 315
EP  - 316
VL  - 7
IS  - 4
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The article examines the gastro-economic theory, an unusually simple, straightforward, institutional theory of self-generating, self-perpetuating business cycles. The author applies gastro-economic theory to business cycles and economic conditions in the United States and looks at the possible correlation between caloric consumption per capita and gross national product. A discussion is presented about weaknesses of the theory such as its inability to predict the amplitude or periodicity of the cycle and the lack of ways to test the theory.
AB  - The article examines the gastro-economic theory, an unusually simple, straightforward, institutional theory of self-generating, self-perpetuating business cycles. The author applies gastro-economic theory to business cycles and economic conditions in the United States and looks at the possible correlation between caloric consumption per capita and gross national product. A discussion is presented about weaknesses of the theory such as its inability to predict the amplitude or periodicity of the cycle and the lack of ways to test the theory.
