N2  - The article presents updates on several faculty members, universities and associations in the United States. John F. Mee, Mead Johnson Professor of Management at the Indiana University Graduate School of Business, was elected International Vice President of the Society for Advancement of Management. Wilford L. White, director of the Office of Business Management Services at Small Business Administration, retired on August 28, 1964 to start work at Howard University. Robert J. House has accepted the position of Executive Director of the McKinsey Foundation for Management Research.
